{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"You'll be happy to know that\nI'll be talking not about my own tragedy,"},{"time":4956,"text":"but other people's tragedy."},{"time":6281,"text":"It's a lot easier to be lighthearted\nabout other people's tragedy"},{"time":9374,"text":"than your own,"},{"time":10549,"text":"and I want to keep it\nin the spirit of the conference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15069,"text":"So, if you believe the media accounts,"},{"time":17262,"text":"being a drug dealer in the height\nof the crack cocaine epidemic"},{"time":21839,"text":"was a very glamorous life,\nin the words of Virginia Postrel."},{"time":25689,"text":"There was money,\nthere was drugs, guns, women,"},{"time":29892,"text":"you know, you name it -- jewelry,\nbling-bling -- it had it all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34181,"text":"What I'm going to tell you today is that,\nin fact, based on 10 years of research,"},{"time":39669,"text":"a unique opportunity\nto go inside a gang --"},{"time":42152,"text":"to see the actual books,\nthe financial records of the gang --"},{"time":45084,"text":"that the answer turns out not to be"},{"time":47476,"text":"that being in the gang\nwas a glamorous life."},{"time":51000,"text":"But I think, more realistically,\nthat being in a gang --"},{"time":53775,"text":"selling drugs for a gang -- is perhaps\nthe worst job in all of America."},{"time":57705,"text":"And that's what I'd like\nto convince you of today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60594,"text":"So there are three things I want to do."},{"time":62529,"text":"First, I want to explain\nhow and why crack cocaine"},{"time":66261,"text":"had such a profound influence\non inner-city gangs."},{"time":71794,"text":"Secondly, I want to tell you"},{"time":73625,"text":"how somebody like me\ncame to be able to see"},{"time":78525,"text":"the inner workings of a gang --\nan interesting story, I think."},{"time":81906,"text":"And then third, I want to tell you,\nin a very superficial way,"},{"time":84840,"text":"about some of the things we found"},{"time":86451,"text":"when we actually got to look\nat the financial records,"},{"time":89039,"text":"the books, of the gang."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90751,"text":"So before I do that, just one warning,"},{"time":94204,"text":"which is that this presentation\nhas been rated 'R'"},{"time":97962,"text":"by the Motion Picture\nAssociation of America."},{"time":100552,"text":"It contains adult themes, adult language."},{"time":103710,"text":"Given who is up on the stage,\nyou'll be delighted to know"},{"time":106434,"text":"that, in fact, there'll be no nudity --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":111417,"text":"Unexpected wardrobe malfunctions aside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114024,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":118962,"text":"So let me start by talking\nabout crack cocaine,"},{"time":122519,"text":"and how it transformed the gang."},{"time":124501,"text":"To do that, you have to actually go\nback to a time before crack cocaine,"},{"time":127929,"text":"in the early '80s, and look at it\nfrom the perspective of a gang leader."},{"time":131363,"text":"Being a gang leader in the inner city\nwasn't such a bad deal in the mid-'80s --"},{"time":137327,"text":"the early '80s, let me say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138844,"text":"Now, you had a lot of power,\nand you got to beat people up --"},{"time":141767,"text":"you got a lot of prestige,\na lot of respect."},{"time":144323,"text":"But the thing is,\nthere was no money in it."},{"time":146900,"text":"The gang had no way to make money."},{"time":148585,"text":"You couldn't charge dues\nto the people in the gang,"},{"time":151011,"text":"because the people in the gang\ndidn't have any money."},{"time":153645,"text":"You couldn't really make any money\nselling marijuana --"},{"time":156277,"text":"marijuana's too cheap, it turns out."},{"time":158697,"text":"You can't get rich selling marijuana."},{"time":160587,"text":"You couldn't sell cocaine;"},{"time":162402,"text":"cocaine's a great product --\npowdered cocaine --"},{"time":164840,"text":"but you've got to know rich white people."},{"time":166830,"text":"And most of the inner-city gang members\ndidn't know any rich white people,"},{"time":170347,"text":"so couldn't sell to that market."},{"time":171910,"text":"You couldn't really do\npetty crime, either."},{"time":173954,"text":"Turns out, petty crime's\na terrible way to make a living."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176653,"text":"As a result, as a gang leader,\nyou had, you know, power --"},{"time":179832,"text":"it's a pretty good life --\nbut the thing was, in the end,"},{"time":182547,"text":"you were living at home with your mother."},{"time":184538,"text":"And so it wasn't really a career."},{"time":186245,"text":"There were limits to how powerful\nand important you could be"},{"time":189107,"text":"if you had to live at home\nwith your mother."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191203,"text":"Then along comes crack cocaine."},{"time":194306,"text":"And in the words of Malcolm Gladwell,"},{"time":197345,"text":"crack cocaine was the extra-chunky\nversion of tomato sauce"},{"time":201800,"text":"for the inner city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202975,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":204000,"text":"Because crack cocaine\nwas an unbelievable innovation."},{"time":206528,"text":"I don't have time to talk about it today,\nbut if you think about it,"},{"time":209773,"text":"I would say that in the last 25 years,"},{"time":211640,"text":"of every invention or innovation\nthat's occurred in this country,"},{"time":214800,"text":"the biggest one in terms of impact"},{"time":216603,"text":"on the well-being of people\nwho live in the inner city,"},{"time":220493,"text":"was crack cocaine."},{"time":221668,"text":"And for the worse --\nnot for the better, but for the worse."},{"time":224473,"text":"It had a huge impact on life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225951,"text":"So what was it about crack cocaine?"},{"time":227839,"text":"It was a brilliant way\nof getting the brain high."},{"time":232434,"text":"Because you could smoke crack cocaine --\nyou can't smoke powdered cocaine --"},{"time":238000,"text":"and smoking is a much more efficient\nmechanism of delivering a high"},{"time":241409,"text":"than snorting it."},{"time":242936,"text":"And it turned out there was this audience\nthat didn't know it wanted crack cocaine,"},{"time":247409,"text":"but when it came, it really did."},{"time":249205,"text":"And it was a perfect drug;"},{"time":250634,"text":"you could buy the cocaine\nthat went into it for a dollar,"},{"time":254834,"text":"sell it for five dollars."},{"time":256343,"text":"Highly addictive --\nthe high was very short."},{"time":258695,"text":"So for fifteen minutes,\nyou get this great high,"},{"time":261391,"text":"and then when you come down,"},{"time":262772,"text":"all you want to do is get high again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265492,"text":"It created a wonderful market."},{"time":267406,"text":"And for the people who were there\nrunning the gang,"},{"time":270562,"text":"it was a great way, seemingly,\nto make a lot of money."},{"time":274000,"text":"At least for the people on the top."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276209,"text":"So this is where we enter the picture."},{"time":278091,"text":"Not really me -- I'm really\na bit player in all this."},{"time":280620,"text":"My co-author, Sudhir Venkatesh,\nis the main character."},{"time":283509,"text":"He was a math major in college\nwho had a good heart,"},{"time":289000,"text":"and decided he wanted\nto get a sociology PhD,"},{"time":291785,"text":"came to the University of Chicago."},{"time":293438,"text":"Now, the three months\nbefore he came to Chicago,"},{"time":296092,"text":"he had spent following the Grateful Dead."},{"time":298647,"text":"And in his own words,\nhe \"looked like a freak.\""},{"time":302138,"text":"He's a South Asian --\nvery dark-skinned South Asian."},{"time":306350,"text":"Big man, and he had hair,\nin his words, \"down to his ass.\""},{"time":310795,"text":"Defied all kinds of boundaries:"},{"time":312538,"text":"Was he black or white?\nWas he man or woman?"},{"time":314800,"text":"He was really a curious sight to be seen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318000,"text":"So he showed up\nat the University of Chicago,"},{"time":320159,"text":"and the famous sociologist\nWilliam Julius Wilson"},{"time":322866,"text":"was doing a book that involved\nsurveying people all across Chicago."},{"time":328514,"text":"He took one look at Sudhir, who was going\nto go do some surveys for him,"},{"time":332162,"text":"and decided he knew exactly\nthe place to send him,"},{"time":334556,"text":"which was to one of the toughest,\nmost notorious housing projects"},{"time":337704,"text":"not just in Chicago,\nbut in the entire United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340219,"text":"So Sudhir, the suburban boy who had never\nreally been in the inner city,"},{"time":343912,"text":"dutifully took his clipboard\nand walked down to this housing project,"},{"time":348839,"text":"gets to the first building."},{"time":350767,"text":"The first building?\nWell, there's nobody there."},{"time":353264,"text":"But he hears some voices\nup in the stairwell,"},{"time":356418,"text":"so he climbs up the stairwell,\ncomes around the corner,"},{"time":360000,"text":"and finds a group of young\nAfrican-American men playing dice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365293,"text":"This is about 1990,\npeak of the crack epidemic."},{"time":368296,"text":"This is a very dangerous job,\nbeing in a gang."},{"time":370478,"text":"You don't like to be surprised."},{"time":372017,"text":"You don't like to be surprised\nby people who come around the corner."},{"time":375554,"text":"And the mantra was:\nshoot first; ask questions later."},{"time":378902,"text":"Now, Sudhir was lucky --\nhe was such a freak,"},{"time":381108,"text":"and that clipboard\nprobably saved his life,"},{"time":383343,"text":"because they figured no other\nrival gang member"},{"time":385590,"text":"would be coming up to shoot\nat them with a clipboard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388109,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":389134,"text":"So his greeting was not particularly\nwarm, but they did say,"},{"time":392189,"text":"well, OK -- let's hear\nyour questions on your survey."},{"time":396260,"text":"So -- I kid you not --"},{"time":397489,"text":"the first question on the survey\nthat he was sent to ask was:"},{"time":401300,"text":"\"How do you feel about being\npoor and Black in America?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":404030,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":407185,"text":"Makes you wonder about academics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408900,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":410828,"text":"So the choice of answers were:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":412733,"text":"[A) Very Good B) Good C) Bad D) Very Bad]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":416404,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":418429,"text":"What Sudhir found out is, in fact,\nthat the real answer was the following:"},{"time":421958,"text":"[A) Very Good B) Good C) Bad\nD) Very Bad E) Fuck you]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":424857,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":426478,"text":"The survey was not, in the end, going\nto be what got Sudhir off the hook."},{"time":430022,"text":"He was held hostage\novernight in the stairwell."},{"time":433526,"text":"There was a lot of gunfire,"},{"time":434855,"text":"there were a lot of philosophical\ndiscussions he had with the gang members."},{"time":438498,"text":"By morning, the gang leader arrived,"},{"time":440272,"text":"checked out Sudhir,\ndecided he was no threat,"},{"time":442414,"text":"and they let him go home."},{"time":443660,"text":"So Sudhir went home,\ntook a shower, took a nap."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446812,"text":"And you and I, probably, faced\nwith the situation, would think,"},{"time":451635,"text":"\"I guess I'm going to write\nmy dissertation on The Grateful Dead,"},{"time":454731,"text":"I've been following them\nfor the last three months.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":457194,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":458226,"text":"Sudhir, on the other hand,"},{"time":459509,"text":"got right back, walked\ndown to the housing project,"},{"time":461954,"text":"went up to the second floor,"},{"time":463321,"text":"and said: \"Hey, guys, I had so much fun\nhanging out with you last night,"},{"time":467247,"text":"I wonder if I could do it again tonight.\""},{"time":469249,"text":"And that was the beginning of what turned\nout to be a beautiful relationship"},{"time":472904,"text":"that involved Sudhir living in the housing\nproject on and off for 10 years,"},{"time":476523,"text":"hanging out in crack houses,\ngoing to jail with the gang members,"},{"time":481302,"text":"having the windows shot out of his car,"},{"time":483864,"text":"having the police break into his apartment\nand steal his computer disks --"},{"time":487386,"text":"you name it."},{"time":488568,"text":"But ultimately, the story\nhas a happy ending for Sudhir,"},{"time":491408,"text":"who became one of the most\nrespected sociologists in the country."},{"time":494675,"text":"And especially for me,"},{"time":496068,"text":"as I sat in my office\nwith my Excel spreadsheet open,"},{"time":499511,"text":"waiting for Sudhir to come and deliver\nto me the latest load of data"},{"time":502872,"text":"that he would get from the gang."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504782,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":508575,"text":"It was one of the most unequal\nco-authoring relationships ever --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":512003,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":513047,"text":"But I was glad to be\nthe beneficiary of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516562,"text":"So what did we find?"},{"time":518389,"text":"What did we find in the gang?"},{"time":520771,"text":"Well, let me say one thing:"},{"time":522481,"text":"We really got access\nto everybody in the gang."},{"time":526108,"text":"We got an inside look at the gang,\nfrom the very bottom up to the very top."},{"time":530456,"text":"They trusted Sudhir, in ways\nthat really no academic has ever --"},{"time":535466,"text":"or really anybody, any outsider --\nhas ever earned the trust of these gangs,"},{"time":540042,"text":"to the point where they actually opened up"},{"time":542523,"text":"what was most interesting\nfor me -- their books,"},{"time":544804,"text":"the financial records they kept."},{"time":546367,"text":"They made them available to us,\nand we not only could study them,"},{"time":549463,"text":"but we could ask them questions\nabout what was in them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552083,"text":"So if I have to kind of summarize\nvery quickly in the short time I have"},{"time":555533,"text":"what the bottom line of what\nI take away from the gang is,"},{"time":559507,"text":"it's that, if I had to draw\na parallel between the gang"},{"time":562241,"text":"and any other organization,"},{"time":564384,"text":"it would be that the gang\nis just like McDonald's,"},{"time":567699,"text":"in a lot of different respects --\nthe restaurant McDonald's."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570572,"text":"So first, in one way,"},{"time":572214,"text":"which isn't maybe the most interesting\nway, but it's a good way to start --"},{"time":575853,"text":"is in the way it's organized,\nthe hierarchy of the gang,"},{"time":578523,"text":"the way it looks."},{"time":579698,"text":"So here's what the org chart\nof the gang looks like."},{"time":582176,"text":"I don't know if you know much\nabout org charts,"},{"time":584407,"text":"but if you were to assign a stripped-down\nand simplified McDonald's org chart,"},{"time":588138,"text":"this is exactly what it would look like."},{"time":590116,"text":"It's amazing, but the top\nlevel of the gang,"},{"time":592334,"text":"they actually call themselves\nthe \"Board of Directors.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":594985,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":596088,"text":"And Sudhir says"},{"time":598059,"text":"it's not like these guys\nhad a very sophisticated view"},{"time":601477,"text":"of what happened\nin American corporate life,"},{"time":604966,"text":"but they had seen movies\nlike \"Wall Street,\""},{"time":607055,"text":"and they had learned a little bit\nabout what it was like"},{"time":610454,"text":"to be in the real world."},{"time":612429,"text":"Now, below that board of directors,"},{"time":614287,"text":"you've got essentially\nwhat are regional VPs --"},{"time":616716,"text":"people who control, say, the South Side\nof Chicago, or the West Side of Chicago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620525,"text":"Sudhir got to know very well the guy\nwho had the unfortunate assignment"},{"time":624000,"text":"of trying to take the Iowa franchise,"},{"time":626363,"text":"which, it turned out, for this black gang,"},{"time":628448,"text":"was not one of the more brilliant\nfinancial endeavors they undertook."}]},{"cues":[{"time":632570,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":633848,"text":"But the thing that really makes the gang\nseem like McDonald's is its franchisees."},{"time":638168,"text":"The guys who are running\nthe local gangs --"},{"time":642532,"text":"the four-square-block\nby four-square-block areas --"},{"time":645507,"text":"they're just like the guys, in some sense,\nwho are running the McDonald's."},{"time":649033,"text":"They are the entrepreneurs."},{"time":650526,"text":"They get the exclusive property rights\nto control the drug-selling."},{"time":654286,"text":"They get the name of the gang behind them,\nfor merchandising and marketing."},{"time":661298,"text":"And they're the ones who basically\nmake the profit or lose a profit,"},{"time":664663,"text":"depending on how good\nthey are at running the business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667266,"text":"Now, the group I really want you\nto think about, though,"},{"time":670195,"text":"are the ones at the bottom --\nthe foot soldiers."},{"time":672472,"text":"These are the teenagers, typically,"},{"time":674544,"text":"who'd be standing out on the street\ncorner, selling the drugs."},{"time":677592,"text":"Extremely dangerous work."},{"time":680036,"text":"And important to note is that almost all\nof the weight, all of the people"},{"time":685438,"text":"in this organization are at the bottom --\njust like McDonald's."},{"time":688519,"text":"So in some sense, the foot soldiers\nare a lot like the people"},{"time":691503,"text":"who are taking your order at McDonald's,"},{"time":693493,"text":"and it's not just by chance\nthat they're like them."},{"time":695955,"text":"In fact, in these neighborhoods,\nthey'd be the same people."},{"time":698780,"text":"So the same kids who are working\nin the gang were actually,"},{"time":701705,"text":"at the very same time,\ntypically working part-time"},{"time":704488,"text":"at a place like McDonald's."},{"time":706043,"text":"Which already foreshadows\nthe main result that I've talked about,"},{"time":709458,"text":"about what a crappy job\nit was, being in the gang."},{"time":712572,"text":"Because obviously, if being in the gang\nwere such a wonderful, lucrative job,"},{"time":716247,"text":"why in the world would these guys\nmoonlight at McDonald's?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":719515,"text":"So what do the wages look like?\nYou might be surprised."},{"time":722587,"text":"But based on being able to talk to them\nand to see their records,"},{"time":726238,"text":"this is what it looks\nlike in terms of the wages."},{"time":728732,"text":"The hourly wage the foot soldiers\nwere earning was $3.50 an hour."},{"time":732846,"text":"It was below the minimum wage.\nAnd this is well-documented."},{"time":736259,"text":"It's easy to see by the patterns\nof consumption they have."},{"time":739146,"text":"It really is not fiction -- it's fact."},{"time":742145,"text":"There was very little money in the gang,\nespecially at the bottom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746000,"text":"Now if you managed to rise up, say,\nand be that local leader,"},{"time":749409,"text":"the guy who's the equivalent\nof the McDonald's franchisee,"},{"time":752170,"text":"you'd be making 100,000 dollars a year."},{"time":754079,"text":"And that, in some ways,\nwas the best job you could hope to get"},{"time":757429,"text":"if you were growing up in one of these\nneighborhoods as a young black male."},{"time":761111,"text":"If you managed to rise to the very top,"},{"time":763030,"text":"200,000 or 400,000 dollars a year\nis what you'd hope to make."},{"time":765979,"text":"Truly, you would be a great success story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768732,"text":"And one of the sad parts\nof this is that, indeed,"},{"time":771832,"text":"among the many other\nramifications of crack cocaine"},{"time":774401,"text":"is that the most talented individuals\nin these communities --"},{"time":778555,"text":"this is what they were striving for."},{"time":780310,"text":"They weren't trying to make it\nin legitimate ways,"},{"time":782802,"text":"because there were\nno legitimate channels out."},{"time":785016,"text":"This was the best way out."},{"time":786413,"text":"And it actually was\nthe right choice, probably,"},{"time":789108,"text":"to try to make it out this way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793117,"text":"You look at this,"},{"time":794425,"text":"the relationship to McDonald's\nbreaks down here."},{"time":797368,"text":"The money looks about the same."},{"time":799327,"text":"Why is it such a bad job?"},{"time":800793,"text":"Well, the reason it's such a bad job\nis that there's somebody shooting at you"},{"time":804533,"text":"a lot of the time."},{"time":806119,"text":"So, with shooting at you,\nwhat are the death rates?"},{"time":809000,"text":"We found, in our gang --"},{"time":810181,"text":"and admittedly, this was not really\na standard situation;"},{"time":813441,"text":"this was a time of intense violence,\nof a lot of gang wars,"},{"time":817907,"text":"as this gang actually\nbecame quite successful."},{"time":820590,"text":"But there were costs."},{"time":821850,"text":"And so the death rate --"},{"time":823619,"text":"not to mention the rate of being arrested,\nsent to prison, being wounded --"},{"time":828603,"text":"the death rate in our sample\nwas seven percent per person per year."},{"time":833332,"text":"You're in the gang for four years,"},{"time":835087,"text":"you expect to die\nwith about a 25 percent likelihood."},{"time":839627,"text":"That is about as high as you can get."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841753,"text":"So for comparison's purposes,"},{"time":843624,"text":"let's think about some other walk of life\nyou may expect might be extremely risky."},{"time":848650,"text":"Let's say that you were a murderer"},{"time":850666,"text":"and you were convicted of murder,\nand you're sent to death row."},{"time":853891,"text":"It turns out, the death rates on death row\nfrom all causes, including execution:"},{"time":857884,"text":"two percent a year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859064,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":860089,"text":"So it's a lot safer being on death row"},{"time":863746,"text":"than it is selling drugs\nout on the street."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866844,"text":"That gives you some pause,\nfor those of you who believe"},{"time":869746,"text":"that a death penalty's going to have\nan enormous deterrent effect on crime."},{"time":875556,"text":"To give you a sense of just how bad\nthe inner city was during crack --"},{"time":878895,"text":"and I'm not really focusing\non the negatives,"},{"time":881653,"text":"but really, there's another story\nto tell you there --"},{"time":884597,"text":"if you look at the death rates\njust of random, young black males"},{"time":888359,"text":"growing up in the inner city\nin the United States,"},{"time":890770,"text":"the death rates during crack\nwere about one percent."},{"time":893570,"text":"That's extremely high."},{"time":894746,"text":"And this is violent death --\nit's unbelievable, in some sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":897761,"text":"To put it into perspective: if you compare\nthis to the soldiers in Iraq,"},{"time":902515,"text":"for instance, right now\nfighting the war: 0.5 percent."},{"time":906205,"text":"So in some very literal way,"},{"time":909266,"text":"the young black men who were\ngrowing up in this country"},{"time":912198,"text":"were living in a war zone,"},{"time":914035,"text":"very much in the sense that the soldiers\nover in Iraq are fighting in a war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":920829,"text":"So why in the world, you might ask,"},{"time":923868,"text":"would anybody be willing\nto stand out on a street corner"},{"time":927687,"text":"selling drugs for $3.50 an hour,"},{"time":930000,"text":"with a 25 percent chance of dying\nover the next four years?"},{"time":933000,"text":"Why would they do that?"},{"time":934959,"text":"And I think there are a couple answers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937806,"text":"I think the first one\nis that they got fooled by history."},{"time":943513,"text":"It used to be the gang\nwas a rite of passage;"},{"time":945854,"text":"that the young people controlled the gang;"},{"time":947912,"text":"that as you got older,\nyou dropped out of the gang."},{"time":951463,"text":"So what happened was,"},{"time":952663,"text":"the people who happened to be\nin the right place at the right time --"},{"time":955965,"text":"the people who happened to be leading\nthe gang in the mid-to-late-'80s --"},{"time":961405,"text":"became very, very wealthy."},{"time":963388,"text":"And so the logical thing to think"},{"time":965516,"text":"was that they are going\nto age out of the gang"},{"time":968664,"text":"like everybody else has,"},{"time":969885,"text":"and the next generation is going\nto take over and get the wealth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":973024,"text":"There are striking similarities,\nI think, to the Internet boom."},{"time":976033,"text":"The first set of people in Silicon Valley\ngot very, very rich."},{"time":979283,"text":"And then all of my friends said,\n\"Maybe I should go do that, too.\""},{"time":983397,"text":"And they were willing to work very cheap\nfor stock options that never came."},{"time":988025,"text":"In some sense,\nthat's what happened, exactly,"},{"time":990423,"text":"to the set of people we were looking at."},{"time":993961,"text":"They were willing to start at the bottom,"},{"time":996180,"text":"just like, say, a first-year\nlawyer at a law firm"},{"time":999261,"text":"is willing to start at the bottom,"},{"time":1001456,"text":"work 80-hour weeks\nfor not that much money,"},{"time":1003543,"text":"because they think\nthey're going to make partner."},{"time":1005876,"text":"But the rules changed,\nand they never got to make partner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1008686,"text":"Indeed, the same people who were running\nall of the major gangs in the late 1980s"},{"time":1012569,"text":"are still running the major gangs\nin Chicago today."},{"time":1014999,"text":"They never passed on any of the wealth,"},{"time":1016906,"text":"So everybody got stuck\nat that $3.50-an-hour job,"},{"time":1019774,"text":"and it turned out to be a disaster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022310,"text":"The other thing the gang was\nvery good at was marketing and trickery."},{"time":1026597,"text":"And so for instance,\none thing the gang would do is --"},{"time":1030269,"text":"the gang leaders would have\nbig entourages,"},{"time":1032525,"text":"and they'd drive fancy cars\nand have fancy jewelry."},{"time":1035761,"text":"So what Sudhir eventually realized\nas he hung out with them more,"},{"time":1038871,"text":"is that, really, they didn't own\nthose cars -- they just leased them,"},{"time":1042155,"text":"because they couldn't afford\nto own the fancy cars."},{"time":1044858,"text":"And they didn't really have gold jewelry,\nthey had gold-plated jewelry."},{"time":1048344,"text":"It goes back to, you know,\nthe real-real versus the fake-real."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051728,"text":"And really, they did all sorts\nof things to trick the young people"},{"time":1055714,"text":"into thinking what a great deal\nthe gang was going to be."},{"time":1058531,"text":"So for instance, they would give\na 14-year-old kid"},{"time":1061346,"text":"a whole roll of bills to hold."},{"time":1064496,"text":"That 14-year-old kid\nwould say to his friends,"},{"time":1067350,"text":"\"Hey, look at all the money\nI got in the gang.\""},{"time":1069581,"text":"It wasn't his money -- until he spent it,"},{"time":1071582,"text":"and then he was in debt to the gang,"},{"time":1073325,"text":"and was sort of an indentured\nservant for a while."},{"time":1075738,"text":"So I have a couple minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1077312,"text":"Let me do one last thing\nI hadn't thought I'd have time to do,"},{"time":1081381,"text":"which is to talk about what we learned\nmore generally about economics,"},{"time":1086659,"text":"from the study of the gang."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1088690,"text":"So, economists tend to talk\nin technical words."},{"time":1092269,"text":"Often, our theories fail quite miserably\nwhen we over the data,"},{"time":1095894,"text":"but what's kind of interesting\nis that in this setting,"},{"time":1098704,"text":"it turned out that\nsome of the economic theories"},{"time":1101045,"text":"that worked not so well\nin the real economy"},{"time":1103204,"text":"worked very well in the drug economy,"},{"time":1105418,"text":"in some sense, because\nit's unfettered capitalism."},{"time":1107808,"text":"Here's an economic principle."},{"time":1109225,"text":"This is one of the basic ideas\nin labor economics,"},{"time":1111591,"text":"called a \"compensating differential.\""},{"time":1113399,"text":"It's the idea that the increment to wages\nthat a worker requires"},{"time":1116865,"text":"to leave him indifferent\nbetween performing two tasks,"},{"time":1119503,"text":"one which is more unpleasant\nthan the other."},{"time":1121632,"text":"Compensating differential -- it's why\nwe think garbagemen might be paid more"},{"time":1125302,"text":"than people who work in parks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1126860,"text":"The words of one of the members\nof the gang, I think, make this clear."},{"time":1132806,"text":"So it turns out -- I'm sort\nof getting ahead of myself --"},{"time":1135520,"text":"it turns out, in the gang,\nwhen there's a war going on,"},{"time":1138697,"text":"they actually pay the foot soldiers\ntwice as much money."},{"time":1141738,"text":"It's exactly this concept."},{"time":1143051,"text":"Because they're not willing to be at risk."},{"time":1145707,"text":"And the words of a gang member\ncapture it quite nicely, he says:"},{"time":1148753,"text":"\"Would you stand around here when all\nthis shit ...\" -- the shooting --"},{"time":1152127,"text":"\"... if all this shit's\ngoing on? No, right?"},{"time":1154264,"text":"So if I gonna be asked to put my life\non the line, then front me the cash, man.\""},{"time":1158094,"text":"I think the gang member says it\nmuch more articulately"},{"time":1160666,"text":"than the economist, about what's going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1162707,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1164346,"text":"Here's another one."},{"time":1166000,"text":"Economists talk about game theory,"},{"time":1167666,"text":"that every two-person game\nhas a Nash equilibrium."},{"time":1170048,"text":"Here's the translation\nyou get from the gang member."},{"time":1172530,"text":"They're talking about the decision\nof why they don't go shoot --"},{"time":1175907,"text":"One thing that turns out to be a great\nbusiness tactic in the gang:"},{"time":1179797,"text":"if you go and just shoot guns in the air\nin the other gang's territory --"},{"time":1183703,"text":"people are afraid to go buy drugs there,"},{"time":1185668,"text":"they're going to come\ninto your neighborhood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1187800,"text":"Here's what he says\nabout why they don't do that:"},{"time":1190120,"text":"\"If we start shooting around there,\nthe other gang's territory,"},{"time":1193165,"text":"nobody, I mean, you dig it,\nnobody gonna step on their turf."},{"time":1196072,"text":"But we gotta be careful,"},{"time":1197248,"text":"'cause they can shoot around here too\nand then we all fucked.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1200198,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1201223,"text":"So that's the same concept."},{"time":1202545,"text":"Then again, sometimes\neconomists get it wrong."},{"time":1204783,"text":"One thing we observed in the data\nis that it looked like --"},{"time":1209478,"text":"the gang leader always got paid."},{"time":1212782,"text":"No matter how bad it was economically,\nhe always got himself paid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1217258,"text":"We had some theories related to cash flow,"},{"time":1219432,"text":"and lack of access to capital markets,\nand things like that."},{"time":1222287,"text":"Then we asked the gang member,"},{"time":1223747,"text":"\"Why is it you always get paid\nand your workers don't always get paid?\""},{"time":1227124,"text":"His response is,"},{"time":1228299,"text":"\"You got all these niggers below you\nwho want your job, you dig?"},{"time":1231410,"text":"If you start taking losses,\nthey see you as weak and shit.\""},{"time":1234217,"text":"And I thought about it and said,"},{"time":1235789,"text":"\"CEOs often pay themselves\nmillion-dollar bonuses,"},{"time":1239454,"text":"even when companies\nare losing a lot of money."},{"time":1241790,"text":"And it never would really occur\nto an economist"},{"time":1244029,"text":"that this idea of 'weak and shit'\ncould really be important.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1246949,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1250239,"text":"Maybe \"weak and shit\" is an important\nhypothesis that needs more analysis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1256000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1257175,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}